<hr>
<br>
<p>
<b>NodMutDB</b> is a comprehensive database for the plant and bacterial mutants/genes that affect nodulation and nitrogen fixation.
The collected data in the database are curated from the literature.
</p>

<br>

<p><b>Plants and bacteria curated:</b></p>
<blockquote>
<table class=data align=left border="1" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="1" width=500>
	<tr><th class=data width=50%>Host Plants</th><th class=data width=50%>Bacteria</th></tr>
	<tr><td class=data align=center><a title="Link to Taxonomy Browser at NCBI" href=http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/Taxonomy/Browser/wwwtax.cgi?id=3880 target=_blank><b><i>Medicago truncatula</i></b></a> (barrel medic)</td>
	<td class=data align=center><a title="Link to Taxonomy Browser at NCBI" href=http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/Taxonomy/Browser/wwwtax.cgi?id=382 target=_blank><b><i>Sinorhizobium meliloti</i></b></a></td></tr>
	<tr><td class=data align=center><a title="Link to Taxonomy Browser at NCBI" href=http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/Taxonomy/Browser/wwwtax.cgi?id=3847 target=_blank><b><i>Glycine max</i></b></a> (soybean)</td>
	<td  class=data align=center><a title="Link to Taxonomy Browser at NCBI" href=http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/Taxonomy/Browser/wwwtax.cgi?id=224911 target=_blank><b><i>Bradyrhizobium japonicum</i></b></a></td></tr>
</table>
</blockquote>
